ical philosophy to be the necessary starting point for an adequate inquiry into divine revelation. Lewis Fallis is an independent scholar of political theory.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aRevelation. 4aHistory of Religion. 4aPhilosophy. 4aPolitics & Economics. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh  aDivine revelation.  aEuthyphro.  aInquiry.  aIon.  aJustice.  aKnowledge.  aPlato's dialogues.  aPolitical philosophy.  aSocrates.  aWisdom.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311143106240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781787442702?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781787442702423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781787442702/original  a978-3-11-143106-2  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles